title: Rocketry — Yohannes Aklilu
snippet: As part of Stanford's Space Initiative program, I designed and built an L1 model rocket that successfully reached an altitude of 2000 feet in the atmosphere. This project allowed me to apply aerodynamics, structural engineering, and physics principles to create a high-performance rocket capable of stable flight and recovery.
